  "prompt": "When will the AAP donation list be online again?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, I don't have specific information regarding the status or upcoming availability of the AAP (American Academy of Pediatrics) donation list. To get the most accurate and up-to-date information, I recommend the following steps:\n\n1. **Visit the Official AAP Website:** Check the [American Academy of Pediatrics official website](https://www.aap.org/) for any announcements or updates related to their donation platforms.\n\n2. **Contact AAP Directly:**\n   - **Phone:** You can call their main office or the specific department handling donations.\n   - **Email:** Look for a contact email on their website to inquire directly about the donation list.\n   - **Social Media:** Sometimes organizations post updates on their social media channels like Twitter, Facebook, or LinkedIn.\n\n3. **Subscribe to Newsletters:** If the AAP offers a newsletter or mailing list, subscribing to it can ensure you receive timely updates about donation opportunities and other initiatives.\n\n4. **Check Partner Organizations:** If the donation list is managed through a partner organization or a specific fundraising platform, visiting that partner's website might provide additional information.\n\nIf you're referring to a different \"AAP\" organization, please provide more context, and I'd be happy to assist further!",
